cs.GT, cs.MA, cs.DC, cs.CE, cs.AI

The paper deals with the design of protocols for exchange of information between markets along a single supply chain, which involves game theory (cs.GT) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the efficiency and revenue of the markets, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The design of the protocols involves optimization and decision-making, which are areas of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with electronic commerce, which could also fall under the category of computer engineering (cs.CE).
